#: ../../../admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-dust.rst:25
msgid ""
"Normally, a drive that is encountering bad sectors will most likely "
"encounter more bad sectors, at an unknown time or location. With dm-dust, "
"the user can use the \"addbadblock\" and \"removebadblock\" messages to add "
"arbitrary bad blocks at new locations, and the \"enable\" and \"disable\" "
"messages to modulate the state of whether the configured \"bad blocks\" will "
"be treated as bad, or bypassed. This allows the pre-writing of test data and "
"metadata prior to simulating a \"failure\" event where bad sectors start to "
"appear."
msgstr ""

